<<<<<Name>>>>> vLLM <<<<</Name>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Small Description>>>>> OpenAI-Compatible LLM Inference Server with Single-Node and Multi-Node Serving <<<<</Small Description>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Description>>>>> This container packages vLLM as a ready-to-run, OpenAI-compatible inference server for serving large language models. It supports single-node serving with tensor parallelism across the GPUs on one machine, as well as multi-node serving with pipeline parallelism coordinated over a Ray cluster. No model is baked into the image — bind your own local weights or point the container at a Hugging Face repo id and let it download and cache the model on first run.

Key Features:
- OpenAI-compatible REST API server for LLM inference
- Tensor-parallel serving across multiple GPUs on a single node
- Pipeline-parallel multi-node serving via a Ray cluster
- Flexible model sourcing: local flat directory, existing Hugging Face cache, or fresh download from the Hub
- Gated model support via Hugging Face token
- CUDA and NCCL support bundled in, tuned for InfiniBand or Ethernet fabrics
- Pass-through support for any additional vLLM server flags <<<<</Description>>>>>
