<<<<<Basic Flags>>>>> A handful of flags cover almost everything you'll need day to day:

        --nv                  Give the container access to your NVIDIA GPU(s).
                              Required for serving; without it, only the
                              container's basic import check will pass.

        --bind src:dst        Make a folder on your machine visible inside the
                              container at path dst. Bind your model weights,
                              or an empty folder to let vLLM download into it:
                                --bind /my/models:/model

        --env KEY=VALUE       Set an environment variable inside the container
                              for this run only, e.g. to pick a model:
                                --env MODEL=meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct
                              or supply a token for gated models:
                                --env HF_TOKEN=<token>

        (For the full list of options, see: apptainer help exec)

<<<<</Basic Flags>>>>>
