<<<<<Modes>>>>> There are four ways to use this container: run it plainly to start the server, exec a specific command, shell in interactively, or launch it as a background instance.

        RUN — start the inference server
        --------------------------------
        Launches the OpenAI-compatible API server, serving whatever MODEL
        points at. The mode name goes at the end of the command; running
        with no mode at all uses the default (serve).

          # Model already in your local Hugging Face cache
          apptainer run --nv \
            --env MODEL=Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B \
            --bind ~/.cache/huggingface:/model/hf-cache \
            container.sif serve

          # Model files in their own flat local directory
          apptainer run --nv \
            --bind /my/models/Qwen3.5-4B:/model \
            container.sif serve

          # Model not downloaded yet — vLLM downloads on first run
          apptainer run --nv \
            --env MODEL=Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B \
            --bind /my/models:/model/hf-cache \
            container.sif serve

          # Extra vLLM flags pass straight through after `serve`
          apptainer run --nv --bind /my/models:/model container.sif serve \
            --max-model-len 8192 --gpu-memory-utilization 0.9

        EXEC — run your own commands
        --------------------------------
        Runs a one-off command inside the container, e.g. to check GPU
        visibility or inspect the environment.

          apptainer exec --nv container.sif nvidia-smi
          apptainer exec --nv container.sif python -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.device_count())"

        SHELL — drop into an interactive prompt
        --------------------------------
        Starts an interactive shell inside the container. No command runs
        automatically — useful for inspecting the environment or installed
        packages.

          apptainer shell --nv --bind /my/models:/model container.sif
          # Type `exit` to leave.

        INSTANCE — run the container as a persistent background service
        --------------------------------
        Starts the container detached, so the inference server keeps
        running after you disconnect.

          apptainer instance start --nv --bind /my/models:/model \
            container.sif vllm-job

          apptainer exec instance://vllm-job curl localhost:8000/v1/models

          apptainer instance list
          apptainer instance stop vllm-job

<<<<</Modes>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Installing Extra Packages>>>>> You can `pip install` something new right inside a running container — it will work for that session. But the container filesystem resets on every fresh run, so anything you installed is gone next time, unless you use an overlay:

        apptainer overlay create --size 1024 overlay.img
        apptainer shell --nv --overlay overlay.img --bind /my/models:/model container.sif
        pip install <package>

        Reuse the same overlay.img next time to see the package again.

<<<<</Installing Extra Packages>>>>>
